sswoman. Her flamboyant personality and reputation for tyrannical behavior earned her the nickname Queen of Mean. ', '\r\nCarlos Enrique Lehder Rivas is a German-Colombian former drug lord who was a co-founder of the Medellin Cartel He is currently imprisoned in the United States.Born in Armenia, Colombia, Lehder eventually ran a cocaine transport empire on Norman\'s Cay island, 210 miles (340 km) off the Florida coast in the central Bahamas. ', 'Jose Gonzalo Rodriguez Gacha also was known by the nickname El Mexicano, was a Colombian drug lord who was one of the leaders of the notorious Medellin Cartel along with the Ochoa Brothers and Pablo Escobar. At the height of his criminal career, Rodriguez was acknowledged as one of the world\'s most successful drug dealers. In 1988, Forbes magazine included him in their annual list of the world\'s billionaires.\r\n. ', '                            \r\nMarcos Arturo Beltran Leyva was an organized crime figure and the leader of the Mexican drug trafficking organization known as the Beltran-Leyva Cartel, which he and his brothers Carlos, Alfredo and Hector founded.\r\nHis cartel was responsible for cocaine, marijuana, heroin and methamphetamine production, transportation, and wholesaling. ', '                       \r\nViktor Anatolyevich Boutis a Russian arms dealer. Bout, an entrepreneur and former Soviet military translator, reportedly used his multiple air transport companies to smuggle weapons since the collapse of communism from Eastern Europe to Africa and the Middle East during the 1990s and early 2000s. Bout was nicknamed the Merchant of Death and Sanctions Buster for his reported wide-reaching operations, extensive clientele, and willingness to bypass embargoes.\r\n', '\r\n\r\nDawood Ibrahim Kaskar is a Mumbai underworld figure, criminal mobster, terrorist and drug dealer most wanted by India with a reward of $25 million over his head, and has been wanted since 1994. He is originally from Dongri in Mumbai, India.\r\n